{"id":25554,"date":"2017-12-06T10:57:22","date_gmt":"2017-12-06T06:57:22","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=25554"},"modified":"2019-05-18T12:21:37","modified_gmt":"2019-05-18T08:21:37","slug":"dua-qiyam-al-layl-takbir","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/06\/dua-qiyam-al-layl-takbir\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Dua: The Prophet&#8217;s night prayer routine"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Shariq al-Hawzani reported: I entered the home of Aisha, may Allah be pleased with her, and I asked her, \u201cHow did the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, begin his prayer when he awakened at night?\u201d Aisha said, \u201cWhen the Prophet awakened at night, he would exalt Allah ten times, praise Allah ten times, and glorify Allah with praises ten times. The Prophet would say ten times: Glory be to the King, the Holy. The Prophet would seek the forgiveness of Allah ten times and declare the oneness of Allah ten times. Then, the Prophet would say ten times: <strong>O Allah, I seek refuge in you from the confinement of the world and the confinement of the Day of Resurrection<\/strong>. Then, he would begin his prayer.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 5085<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0634\u0631\u064a\u0642 \u0627\u0644\u0647\u0648\u0632\u0646\u064a \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u00a0 \u062f\u064e\u062e\u064e\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u0641\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u0628\u0650\u0645\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u064